Mount St. Helens, the volcano that blew its top with cataclysmic force in 1980, erupted for the first time in 18 years Friday, belching a huge column of white steam and ash after days of rumblings.
Heightening the suspense around what a quivering Mount St. Helens may do next -- and delighting the thousands of tourists flocking there -- the volcano on Monday morning spewed a cloud of steam and then sputtered out another picturesque puff later in the day.
